> Entertainment Sotheby's exhibits huge Taubman collection prior to sales Frank Stella's painting "Delaware Crossing," center, and a Henry Moore sculpture, foreround, are among A. Alfred Taubman's 500-piece collection being exhibited before auction at Sotheby's, Friday, Oct. 23, 2015, in New York. The collection will be auctioned over four dedicated sales, three in November and one in January, and estimated to bring more than $500 million. (AP Photo/Bebeto Matthews) 
